						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Varadarāja Perumāḷ shrine in the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga I</p>						

						<p>This inscription which commences with the short <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Pugaḻmādu viḷaṅga</hi> etc., of Kulōttuṅga I stops abruptly after mentioning the king's titles Rājakēsarivarman <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tribhuvanachakravarttigaḷ.</p>						

